  "unmapped_findings": [
    "For martensitic/ferritic steels (study I, 53 batches, phase composition neglected): Cr, Mo, Si increase elastic modulus, C and Ni decrease it; R²=0.96, standard error=1.2 GPa, maximum deviation=3.6 GPa, average deviation=0.8 GPa",
    "For ferritic steels (study II, 35 batches, phase composition calculated by Thermo-Calc): Cr, Mo, Si, Mn increase elastic modulus, cementite shows no effect; R²=0.85, standard error=1.1 GPa, maximum deviation=1.5 GPa, average deviation=0.5 GPa",
    "For austenitic steels (24 batches, phase composition calculated by Thermo-Calc): N, Cr, NbC, TiC increase elastic modulus, Ni and Mo decrease it, Cr23C6 shows no effect; R²=0.83, standard error=2.9 GPa, maximum deviation=3.1 GPa, average deviation=1.1 GPa",
    "Poisson's ratio of untextured steels varies between 0.26 and 0.33, untextured pure iron Poisson's ratio is 0.291, common engineering approximation is 0.3",
    "Reported elastic modulus values: NbC 350-500 GPa, TiC 460 GPa",
    "Figure 1: Regression coefficients of composition on elastic modulus of martensitic/ferritic steels (phase composition neglected), sorted by decreasing significance",
    "Figure 2: Regression coefficients of composition on elastic modulus of ferritic steels (phase composition calculated by Thermo-Calc), sorted by decreasing significance",
    "Figure 3: Regression coefficients of composition on elastic modulus of austenitic steels (phase composition calculated by Thermo-Calc), sorted by decreasing significance"
  ]
}